<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</emphasis>
The microscope slide of 
<taxonomicName box="[611,847,151,176]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[611,847,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Latrunculia tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, kindly supplied by Dr Carsten Lüter, Museum für Naturkund Berlin, is thought to hold spicules from the 
<typeStatus box="[787,888,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
; no preserved specimen has been found despite thorough searching. Examination of the microscleres reveals that this is also a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1165,1244,223,248]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Bomba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1165,1244,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Bomba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1252,1359,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1252,1359,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
; it has the same unusual microscleres with only basal, median and apical whorls. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hentschel" box="[1057,1257,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refString="Hentschel, E. (1929) Die Kiesel- und Hornschwamme des Nordlichen Eismeers. In: Romer, F., Schaudinn, F., Brauer, A. &amp; Arndt, W. (Eds.), Fauna Arctica. Eine Zusammenstellung der arktischen Tierformen mit besonderer Berucksichtigung des Spitzbergen-Gebietes auf Grund der Ergebnisse der Deutschen Expedition in das Nordliche Eismeer im Jahre 1898. 5 (4). G. Fischer, Jena, pp. 857 - 1042, pls. XII - XIV." type="book chapter" year="1929">
Hentschel (
<number box="[1191,1249,260,284]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that the possession of only three ‘girdles’ in 
<taxonomicName box="[560,685,296,320]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[560,575,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[590,685,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguished it from all species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1087,1220,295,320]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1220,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Latrunculia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known at the time. The anisodiscorhabds of 
<taxonomicName box="[432,557,333,356]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[432,447,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[462,557,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly of the same general form as those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1105,1310,332,357]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Bomba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="endeavourensis">
<emphasis box="[1105,1122,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1137,1310,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">endeavourensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">gen. et sp. nov.</emphasis>
; they both possess three distinct whorls and lack a manubrium, subsidiary whorl and an apex. The anisodiscorhabds of 
<taxonomicName box="[384,512,405,428]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[384,401,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[417,512,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[764,970,404,429]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Bomba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="endeavourensis">
<emphasis box="[764,781,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[797,970,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">endeavourensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,1158,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">gen. et sp. nov.</emphasis>
, however, in the shorter length of the megascleres and the shorter length and smaller width of the anisodiscorhabds (
<tableCitation box="[1201,1288,439,464]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="30.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1289,234,544]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="TABLE 5. Spicule dimensions (µm) of Bomba endeavourensis gen. et sp. nov. Paratype data are from 10 spicule measurements each." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF22EDE0FFBB293ACCDBFF04FEDEFF12" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" tableUuid="DF22EDE0FFBB293ACCDBFF04FEDEFF12">
Table 
<number box="[1274,1288,439,464]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.0">5</number>
</tableCitation>
and 
<number box="[1345,1359,439,464]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="6.0">
<tableCitation box="[1345,1359,439,464]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="30.[151,239,1533,1556]" captionTargetBox="[159,1288,1584,1688]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="TABLE 6. Spicule dimensions (µm) of Bomba tricincta (Hentschel, 1929) gen. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF22EDE0FFBB293ACCDBFA61FBADF9C9" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" tableUuid="DF22EDE0FFBB293ACCDBFA61FBADF9C9">6</tableCitation>
</number>
). The ornamentation of the anisodiscorhabds is also quite different, being sharply bifurcate spines in 
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1385,477,500]" class="Demospongiae" family="Latrunculiidae" genus="Latrunculia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tricincta">
<emphasis box="[1255,1272,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1290,1385,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">tricincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No further specimens have been recorded that we know of, thus, the genus is restricted to the north-eastern Pacific Ocean and North Atlantic Ocean above 
<collectingCountry box="[599,691,549,573]" name="Norway" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Norway</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
